Oatmeal Raisin Cookies

Ingredients:
  - 250g (2c) flour
  -   5g (1tsp) baking soda
  -   5g (1tsp) baking powder
  -   5g (1tsp) salt
  - 227g (1c) butter
  - 200g (1c) white sugar
  - 200g (1c) [dark] brown sugar
  -   2 eggs
  -  10mL (2tsp) vanilla extract
  - 270g (3c) old-fashioned oats
  - 250g (1.5c) raisins

Process:
  1. Preheat oven to 350F.
  2. Combine flour, baking soda, and baking powder.
  3. In separate bowl, cream butter and white sugar; add dark brown sugar, then incorporate one egg at a time.
  4. Combine dry and wet ingredients, add vanilla extract.
  5. Gently add oats and raisins.\
  6. Roll 24-36 small balls of dough and space evenly across 2-3 parchment paper covered baking sheets.
  7. Bake 11-13m until edges begin to solidify and brown.

Tips:
  - Always try to use room-temperature ingredients.
  - Be careful not to overwork the batter.
